  "text": "Ϫ/Ϫ macrophages were fully capable of killing B. burgdorferi, similar to our findings with B. hermsii. Together, these results imply the presence of an additional, nonmacrophage, non-B-cell defect in MyD88 Ϫ/Ϫ mice crucial to host defense against B. hermsii. B. hermsii is also highly resistant to complement-mediated killing and to PMN-mediated oxidative killing [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Thus, the MyD88-dependent host defense complementary to antibody-mediated clearance has yet to be identified and will require further studies.",
